-if this is being add, classpath will be added to MANIFEST.MF and jar will be executable -> java -jar MavenPlugins-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar
-if this down is not present (at least <mainClass>) jar won't be executable
-if <addClasspath> is present it will add classpath which consists of references of JAR files in maven local repo (pom) ->
if you want to execute those jar (with dependencies), that jar should be added to target folder (in this case)

--**--
  <plugin>
    <artifactId>maven-jar-plugin</artifactId>
      <configuration>
        <archive>
          <manifest>
            <addClasspath>true</addClasspath>
            <mainClass>HelloWorld</mainClass>
          </manifest>
        </archive>
    </configuration>
  </plugin>

  Manifest-Version: 1.0
  Archiver-Version: Plexus Archiver
  Created-By: Apache Maven 3.6.1
  Built-By: Jean Pierre
  Build-Jdk: 11.0.5
  Class-Path: commons-lang3-3.8.1.jar
  Main-Class: HelloWorld
--**--

